Script to Backup file System

1.Create backup of /etc and /var directories using tar command
2.Compress the backup .tar file using gzip command
3.Write a script to automate backup

tar -cvf /tmp/backup.tar /etc /var   #The /tmp directory in Linux is used for storing temporary files that are created by programs or system processes. These files are usually non-essential and may be automatically deleted after a reboot or after they are no longer needed.


gzip /tmp/backup.tar
